WEBVTT

00:01.968 --> 00:04.938
[jazz music]

00:04.971 --> 00:12.012
♪ ♪

00:20.186 --> 00:22.355
- From the Penn
& Teller Theater

00:22.389 --> 00:24.524
at the Rio Hotel in Las Vegas,

00:24.557 --> 00:28.828
here's our host,
Alyson Hannigan!

00:28.862 --> 00:34.834
[cheers and applause]

00:34.868 --> 00:37.837
[upbeat music]

00:37.871 --> 00:40.340
♪ ♪

00:40.373 --> 00:42.042
- Welcome to "Fool Us."

00:42.075 --> 00:43.276
Penn and Teller always talk

00:43.309 --> 00:45.645
about how much they love
doing this show,

00:45.678 --> 00:48.214
but tonight might
change all that.

00:48.248 --> 00:51.484
This show is Penn
and Teller's nightmare.

00:51.518 --> 00:53.520
We've got two acts
that have already fooled

00:53.553 --> 00:56.089
the boys
a record three times,

00:56.122 --> 00:58.091
another act
who's fooled them twice

00:58.124 --> 01:01.094
and holds the record
for "Fool Us" appearances,

01:01.127 --> 01:04.697
and an old friend of theirs
with an ax to grind.

01:04.731 --> 01:06.599
It should be fun for us

01:06.633 --> 01:09.436
but maybe not so much
for the stars of our show,

01:09.469 --> 01:13.039
the always magical
Penn and Teller!

01:13.073 --> 01:19.045
[cheers and applause]

01:19.079 --> 01:26.119
♪ ♪

01:27.187 --> 01:30.056
Every performer tonight
knows this show,

01:30.090 --> 01:32.959
knows the stakes,
knows Penn and Teller.

01:32.992 --> 01:37.697
Let the games begin with this
familiar three-time Fooler.

01:40.033 --> 01:42.502
- Hi, I'm Jandro from Spain,

01:42.535 --> 01:45.738
and I've won on "Fool Us"
three times.

01:45.772 --> 01:50.009
The first time was very fast.

01:50.043 --> 01:51.511
The second was so fun.

01:51.544 --> 01:54.914
I ended on stage running
with Penn and Teller.

01:54.948 --> 01:56.783
♪ ♪

01:56.816 --> 01:58.218
For my third one,

01:58.251 --> 02:02.889
I did the biggest effect
ever in "Fool Us" history.

02:02.922 --> 02:05.091
[indistinct]
Yeah!

02:05.125 --> 02:09.796
So I had three trophies,
and my life was perfect.

02:09.829 --> 02:11.764
I wanted to share
my happiness,

02:11.798 --> 02:14.868
so I gave one trophy
to each member

02:14.901 --> 02:18.304
of my family:
One for my son,

02:18.338 --> 02:20.740
one for my daughter,

02:20.773 --> 02:23.510
and the last one for my wife.

02:23.543 --> 02:25.979
So now everyone had one.

02:26.012 --> 02:28.248
Well, not everyone.

02:28.281 --> 02:31.684
♪ ♪

02:32.385 --> 02:36.723
[cheers and applause]

02:36.756 --> 02:39.259
- Joining us once again
from Spain,

02:39.292 --> 02:44.397
a three-time Fooler,
here's Jandro!

02:44.430 --> 02:47.767
[cheers and applause]

02:47.800 --> 02:48.968
- Hi, Penn!
Hi, Teller!

02:49.002 --> 02:50.370
Hola, amigos!

02:50.403 --> 02:54.040
Welcome to my TV show,
"Penn and Teller Get Annoyed."

02:54.073 --> 02:56.242
Today, I'm going to try
to do something

02:56.276 --> 02:58.178
no one has ever done.

02:58.211 --> 03:01.114
I'm going
to outclass David Copperfield.

03:01.147 --> 03:02.849
Someone had to do it.

03:02.882 --> 03:07.120
In 1983, David Copperfield
vanished the Statue of Liberty,

03:07.153 --> 03:10.857
great trick, a little bit dark,
but a great trick.

03:10.890 --> 03:15.428
Today, I'm going to vanish
two Statues of Liberty.

03:15.461 --> 03:16.796
Here they are.

03:16.829 --> 03:20.934
♪ ♪

03:20.967 --> 03:23.870
We are going for quantity,
not quality.

03:23.903 --> 03:27.240
But I will vanish them
in the middle

03:27.273 --> 03:29.542
of an airplane landing track

03:29.576 --> 03:32.946
in impossible
laboratory conditions.

03:32.979 --> 03:35.081
And the statues are going
to be held

03:35.114 --> 03:37.350
in midair
by a friend of mine.

03:37.383 --> 03:44.190
♪ ♪

03:44.224 --> 03:46.326
Gracias, Jesus.

03:46.359 --> 03:47.994
♪ ♪

03:48.027 --> 03:51.264
And so that we don't have
legal problems,

03:51.297 --> 03:53.266
we also have a lawyer.

03:53.299 --> 03:56.502
Gracias, Jennifer.

03:56.536 --> 03:59.239
And so that no one steals
those statues,

03:59.272 --> 04:01.241
we also have a policeman.

04:01.274 --> 04:03.509
Gracias, Jose.

04:03.543 --> 04:06.613
♪ ♪

04:06.646 --> 04:09.415
They are going to be
guarding the statues here

04:09.449 --> 04:13.253
in this platform,
totally isolated from the floor

04:13.286 --> 04:16.289
and totally surrounded,
because at the back,

04:16.322 --> 04:18.224
we have two runway controllers.

04:18.258 --> 04:20.226
Hola!
both: Hola!

04:20.260 --> 04:23.396
- And at the front, we have
the Spanish Penn and Teller!

04:23.429 --> 04:26.132
♪ ♪

04:26.165 --> 04:28.067
They could be
your twin brothers.

04:28.101 --> 04:30.870
And from here, you can see,

04:30.903 --> 04:33.506
from the front,
you can see above,

04:33.539 --> 04:35.408
you can see beneath,
you can see the sides,

04:35.441 --> 04:38.011
and you can see
the two runway operators.

04:38.044 --> 04:42.382
Please, if a plane comes,
tell us, so we don't die!

04:42.415 --> 04:44.550
both: Okay!

04:44.584 --> 04:47.687
- And Penn and Teller,
if you see something strange,

04:47.720 --> 04:49.255
you see how the trick works,

04:49.289 --> 04:52.292
or you see something
or someone going in or out,

04:52.325 --> 04:53.926
please stand up and shout,

04:53.960 --> 04:56.629
"Cheater! Cheater!
Tramposo! Tramposo!"

04:56.663 --> 04:59.799
And the landing operators,
if you see someone going in,

04:59.832 --> 05:02.035
going out,
or how the trick works,

05:02.068 --> 05:04.470
please move the banners,
like this, yes.

05:04.504 --> 05:06.439
Mueve, mueve, yeah, sí!

05:06.472 --> 05:08.107
Thank you,
thank you, thank you.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.509
This is totally true.

05:09.542 --> 05:11.377
If they see something strange,

05:11.411 --> 05:13.012
or they know
how the trick is done,

05:13.046 --> 05:15.581
they will start shouting,
and they will screw it up.

05:15.615 --> 05:17.083
I give you my word.

05:17.116 --> 05:20.720
I would give you my blood,
but you are vegan.

05:20.753 --> 05:23.756
So from now on,
we are not going to cut.

05:23.790 --> 05:26.025
It's live, one shot, no edit.

05:26.059 --> 05:28.861
The vanishing
two Statues of Liberty,

05:28.895 --> 05:32.265
totally surrounded,
and in daylight.

05:32.298 --> 05:35.568
Tres, dos, uno!

05:35.601 --> 05:38.571
[dramatic music]

05:38.604 --> 05:45.645
♪ ♪

05:53.686 --> 05:56.823
Sí, sí, sí!

05:56.856 --> 05:58.057
Ha salido!

05:58.091 --> 06:00.860
Have you seen anyone going?
Have you seen?

06:00.893 --> 06:02.095
No?

06:02.128 --> 06:05.531
Have you seen someone?
Come here!

06:05.565 --> 06:07.367
Toca, toca!

06:07.400 --> 06:10.703
Toca--sube, sube!

06:10.737 --> 06:14.474
[indistinct]
Yay!

06:14.507 --> 06:17.009
Sorry, Copperfield!

06:17.043 --> 06:18.277
Bye!

06:18.311 --> 06:24.250
[cheers and applause]

06:26.252 --> 06:29.455
- Jandro!

06:29.489 --> 06:31.991
[cheers and applause]

06:32.024 --> 06:33.393
Jandro.

06:33.426 --> 06:34.961
- Hello!

06:34.994 --> 06:38.331
- Oh, I love you so much.

06:38.364 --> 06:41.267
- Thank you, thank you.
It was very crazy, very crazy.

06:41.300 --> 06:43.603
- Your tricks get bigger
every time.

06:43.636 --> 06:45.138
What comes next?

06:45.171 --> 06:48.241
- Next time,
I'm going to vanish a planet.

06:48.274 --> 06:50.476
- Do you have one in mind?

06:50.510 --> 06:51.677
- I will vanish Pluto

06:51.711 --> 06:54.480
because it's
a very small planet.

06:54.514 --> 06:56.082
- Aww.

06:56.115 --> 06:58.384
They're actually
surprisingly quiet.

06:58.418 --> 07:00.453
They're not really talking.
They're thinking.

07:00.486 --> 07:02.989
- Oh, I've never
seen them thinking.

07:03.022 --> 07:05.491
That's a miracle.

07:05.525 --> 07:07.527
- Well, they're thinking,
but they've got smiles

07:07.560 --> 07:09.395
on their face,
so they are enjoying,

07:09.429 --> 07:10.897
even if they hate you.

07:10.930 --> 07:13.099
- You know,
they are getting a bit old,

07:13.132 --> 07:15.768
so they have to talk more,
you know?

07:15.802 --> 07:17.403
- Okay, Jandro,

07:17.437 --> 07:21.574
let's see if you can run away
with trophy number four.

07:23.042 --> 07:25.244
- Hola, mi amigo!

07:25.278 --> 07:28.214
- Hola, amigos!

07:28.247 --> 07:32.285
- My dear friend, I talk to you
at least every week.

07:32.318 --> 07:33.920
We talk in Spanish.

07:33.953 --> 07:35.988
We talk in English.
We laugh.

07:36.022 --> 07:38.458
You're a very,
very close friend.

07:38.491 --> 07:40.626
We know how you think.

07:40.660 --> 07:43.362
We are not gonna
give you the trophy

07:43.396 --> 07:45.264
that easily this time.

07:45.298 --> 07:46.599
- Okay.

07:46.632 --> 07:49.302
- We have, this time,

07:49.335 --> 07:53.639
a guess on how you did it.

07:53.673 --> 07:57.610
We think--and I'm just gonna
say it outright,

07:57.643 --> 08:00.746
that you masked the bottom
of that with mirrors,

08:00.780 --> 08:04.417
and that there actually
was a hole in the runway,

08:04.450 --> 08:07.053
and they went down
through a trapdoor.

08:08.354 --> 08:10.356
Did we get you?

08:12.058 --> 08:13.626
- You know what's the problem?

08:13.659 --> 08:16.896
- What?
- You know how I think.

08:16.929 --> 08:20.900
But I know how
you think I think.

08:20.933 --> 08:22.802
- Oh!

08:22.835 --> 08:24.904
- So, this time,

08:24.937 --> 08:29.275
this time I have not thought
as I usually think.

08:29.308 --> 08:31.744
- Maybe you wrapped them up
in the cloth.

08:31.777 --> 08:34.046
They're in the cloth
that you threw down afterwards.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.581
- So, so,

08:35.615 --> 08:37.149
I want to see your reaction

08:37.183 --> 08:39.485
when you see
the actual method.

08:39.519 --> 08:43.022
There's an envelope in the
table with the real method.

08:43.055 --> 08:46.259
I wanted you to read
it just for yourselves,

08:46.292 --> 08:47.793
and I want
to see your reaction,

08:47.827 --> 08:50.997
and you decide
if I have fooled you or not.

08:52.198 --> 08:55.601
- Ah!

08:55.635 --> 08:57.470
- I know it's crazy.

08:57.503 --> 08:59.038
- Ah.

09:07.947 --> 09:13.052
- This is the craziest
thing we've ever seen!

09:13.085 --> 09:15.655
No one would ever
do something like that.

09:15.688 --> 09:20.993
It's genius and devilish.

09:21.027 --> 09:23.963
But--this is the first time

09:23.996 --> 09:29.468
I'll be saying this
like this--nos engañaste.

09:29.502 --> 09:31.003
- Thank you.

09:31.037 --> 09:32.004
- What's that mean?
- Thank you.

09:32.038 --> 09:33.539
- What's that mean?

09:33.573 --> 09:35.107
- We are fooled!

09:35.141 --> 09:38.945
- Yay!
Four times!

09:38.978 --> 09:42.248
- Thank you!
- Whoo, Jandro!

09:42.281 --> 09:43.516
- Four times!

09:43.549 --> 09:47.453
- Four-time Fooler Jandro!

09:47.486 --> 09:50.590
Yay!

09:50.623 --> 09:52.325
Whoo!

09:52.358 --> 09:54.093
[sighs]

09:54.126 --> 09:59.065
Penn and Teller just got duped,
deceived, and delighted.

09:59.098 --> 10:01.400
But they've got
three more "Fool Us" veterans

10:01.434 --> 10:04.470
to take on,
as "Fool Us" continues.

10:04.503 --> 10:09.075
[jazz music]

10:12.378 --> 10:16.949
[jazz music]

10:16.983 --> 10:20.252
- Welcome back to Penn
and Teller's worst nightmare.

10:20.286 --> 10:22.688
Boys, I bet you didn't
see this coming.

10:22.722 --> 10:25.925
Take a look.

10:25.958 --> 10:28.694
- Hello, my name's
Piff the Magic Dragon.

10:28.728 --> 10:31.964
Did you know that it all
started for me ten years ago,

10:31.998 --> 10:33.799
when I was on the very
first season

10:33.833 --> 10:35.201
of "Penn & Teller: Fool Us"?

10:35.234 --> 10:37.370
That single appearance
lit my career on fire,

10:37.403 --> 10:38.638
got to America.

10:38.671 --> 10:41.273
I became BFFs
with Penn and Teller.

10:41.307 --> 10:43.309
But when the pages
of history are written,

10:43.342 --> 10:45.778
only one question
will remain--did I,

10:45.811 --> 10:49.248
Piff the Magic Dragon,
fool Penn and Teller?

10:49.281 --> 10:50.983
The answer, of course, is no.

10:51.017 --> 10:52.652
Otherwise, I'd be on my yacht,
like Shim Lin.

10:52.685 --> 10:55.554
Today, I'm here
to make that right.

10:55.588 --> 10:57.923
I want that trophy.
It haunts me.

10:57.957 --> 11:00.693
It's all I can think about.
I see it everywhere I go.

11:00.726 --> 11:02.561
No matter the fame
and the fortune,

11:02.595 --> 11:05.731
it means nothing
till that trophy is mine.

11:05.765 --> 11:09.168
But to get it, I'm gonna have
to perform my best trick yet,

11:09.201 --> 11:12.204
convincing Penn and Teller
we've never met.

11:13.539 --> 11:16.909
[cheers and applause]

11:16.942 --> 11:20.112
- Performing on "Fool Us"
for the first time,

11:20.146 --> 11:23.482
here's Claude
the Regular Dragon.

11:23.516 --> 11:26.852
[upbeat music]

11:26.886 --> 11:30.089
- Good evening, my name is
Claude the Regular Dragon.

11:30.122 --> 11:33.659
Penn, Teller, have you ever met
Claude the Regular Dragon?

11:33.693 --> 11:34.960
- No.

11:34.994 --> 11:36.328
- Consider yourself fooled

11:36.362 --> 11:39.031
because it's actually me,
Piff the Magic Dragon!

11:39.065 --> 11:42.334
Now I'm the champion!
Let's lower the trophy!

11:42.368 --> 11:45.571
Well, fine, plan B.

11:45.604 --> 11:49.175
Standing beside me is the Penn
and Teller Chamber of Sorrows,

11:49.208 --> 11:51.477
containing the one thing
guaranteed to fool

11:51.510 --> 11:52.978
Penn and Teller.

11:53.012 --> 11:55.448
I'll be right back.

11:55.481 --> 11:57.416
Where did I put it?
[cat meows]

11:57.450 --> 11:59.285
It's in here somewhere.

11:59.318 --> 12:01.220
Oh, is it behind this--oh,
there it is.

12:01.253 --> 12:04.990
I've got it.
I'm coming out.

12:05.024 --> 12:08.861
A card trick,
your Achilles heel.

12:08.894 --> 12:11.864
You might as well just lower
that trophy right now, boys.

12:11.897 --> 12:14.567
Let's just lower the trophy.
Fine.

12:14.600 --> 12:16.502
Before we go any further,
I have a plan.

12:16.535 --> 12:18.704
Last time,
I went home empty-handed,

12:18.738 --> 12:19.739
not tonight.

12:19.772 --> 12:21.640
Penn, do you have $20?

12:21.674 --> 12:23.642
- I do happen to, yes.

12:23.676 --> 12:25.444
- Whip it out, Penn.
Whip it out.

12:25.478 --> 12:27.513
Hey Penn,
do you have a pen, Penn?

12:27.546 --> 12:30.282
- I do.
- I got one, too.

12:30.316 --> 12:33.085
Let's use mine
because mine is magic.

12:33.119 --> 12:34.854
You're gonna write your name
on the money.

12:34.887 --> 12:36.155
In fact, I'd like you
to write something

12:36.188 --> 12:38.457
very specific,
"To Piff, love, Penn."

12:38.491 --> 12:40.593
That's me.
- L-U-V or L-O-V-E?

12:40.626 --> 12:43.763
- Just a heart.
- Okay.

12:43.796 --> 12:45.364
- I'm gonna take
the pen back, please.

12:45.397 --> 12:48.768
- Oh, certainly.

12:48.801 --> 12:50.870
- Vanish.

12:50.903 --> 12:55.941
I'm gonna take the money.
Vanish.

12:55.975 --> 12:57.877
Don't look at my pocket.

12:57.910 --> 13:01.747
Now, Penn, if I fool you,
you'll get your money back.

13:01.781 --> 13:04.016
But if I fail,
the money's mine to keep.

13:04.049 --> 13:07.219
Fair?

13:07.253 --> 13:08.954
Teller, I haven't
forgotten you.

13:08.988 --> 13:12.224
Should I fool you, you get
this sweet, sweet trophy.

13:12.258 --> 13:14.894
♪ ♪

13:14.927 --> 13:16.195
Look at that.

13:16.228 --> 13:17.997
Imagine that on your
mantelpiece there, Teller.

13:18.030 --> 13:19.498
♪ ♪

13:19.532 --> 13:20.966
The stage is set.

13:21.000 --> 13:23.469
Alyson, please join me
over here at the table.

13:23.502 --> 13:24.737
- Yes.

13:24.770 --> 13:26.972
- Alyson, I'm gonna deal
these cards before you.

13:27.006 --> 13:28.741
Anytime you like,
you're gonna call out "stop."

13:28.774 --> 13:30.910
Happy?
- Yeah.

13:30.943 --> 13:31.977
- Vanish.

13:32.011 --> 13:33.512
- Amazing.
- Here we go.

13:37.817 --> 13:38.951
- Stop.
- Just here?

13:38.984 --> 13:40.085
- Yeah.

13:40.119 --> 13:41.253
- Are you happy
just there, Alyson?

13:41.287 --> 13:42.354
- Yeah.

13:42.388 --> 13:43.455
- Or would you like me
to continue?

13:43.489 --> 13:44.623
- All right, one more.
- One more?

13:44.657 --> 13:46.292
- One more.

13:46.325 --> 13:47.927
- Alyson, you're gonna
take the three.

13:47.960 --> 13:49.795
That is your card.
I'm gonna slide it towards you.

13:49.829 --> 13:51.831
Do you have a pen?
- No.

13:51.864 --> 13:53.966
- This show is
getting expensive.

13:53.999 --> 13:56.035
Alyson, you're gonna
write your name on the front

13:56.068 --> 13:57.403
of the playing card
for me, please.

13:57.436 --> 13:59.138
- Like--on the face?
- That's a good idea, yeah.

13:59.171 --> 14:00.506
- That's okay?
- Yeah, you nailed it.

14:00.539 --> 14:02.374
It's almost like you've done
this show for however

14:02.408 --> 14:03.909
many seasons it's been.

14:03.943 --> 14:05.578
Once you've done that, Alyson,

14:05.611 --> 14:07.513
I'd like you to place the card
anywhere back in the deck.

14:07.546 --> 14:09.648
Could be literally
anywhere back in the deck.

14:11.483 --> 14:12.852
I'm gonna show the card
to the camera,

14:12.885 --> 14:14.386
so that everyone
gets to see it.

14:14.420 --> 14:17.223
Just there, the three of clubs,
with Alyson's name upon it.

14:17.256 --> 14:20.292
Now Alyson, roughly speaking,
how many cards down in the deck

14:20.326 --> 14:22.528
do you think that was?

14:22.561 --> 14:23.929
Just roughly.
- 20.

14:23.963 --> 14:26.498
- 20 cards, I'm gonna give
the cards another shuffle.

14:29.134 --> 14:32.204
Or did I?

14:32.238 --> 14:34.306
I'm gonna cut the cards.

14:34.340 --> 14:37.743
- Whoa.

14:37.776 --> 14:39.778
- Or did I?

14:39.812 --> 14:43.182
I'm gonna eat one of these
delicious nachos.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.421
Or did I?

14:49.455 --> 14:50.689
Now, Penn, Teller,

14:50.723 --> 14:52.992
if you're fooled,
this whole thing can end now

14:53.025 --> 14:56.795
'cause what follows next is
a convoluted hot mess.

14:56.829 --> 14:58.530
- We'd like the hot mess.
- Oh, you want to continue.

14:58.564 --> 15:01.033
Fine, well, you've only got
yourselves to blame.

15:01.066 --> 15:02.701
Here's what's gonna
happen next, Alyson.

15:02.735 --> 15:04.203
You're gonna start
dealing the cards.

15:04.236 --> 15:06.071
As you deal the cards,
you're gonna count the cards.

15:06.105 --> 15:07.640
One, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:07.673 --> 15:09.174
Two, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:09.208 --> 15:11.210
Three, elephant, elephant,
elephant, etc.

15:11.243 --> 15:12.912
Three elephants per card.

15:12.945 --> 15:14.213
- Okay.
- That's very important.

15:14.246 --> 15:16.048
When you get to your card,
you're gonna stop.

15:16.081 --> 15:18.450
You're gonna remember
your total number of elephants.

15:18.484 --> 15:20.653
Pro tip: Multiply your number
by three elephants.

15:20.686 --> 15:22.254
Is that clear?
- Not at all.

15:22.288 --> 15:24.323
- Great.
This should be interesting.

15:24.356 --> 15:26.392
Alyson, start dealing.

15:26.425 --> 15:27.493
- Okay.

15:27.526 --> 15:29.061
One, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:29.094 --> 15:31.030
Two, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:31.063 --> 15:33.265
Three, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:33.299 --> 15:35.434
Four, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:35.467 --> 15:37.536
Five, elephant, elephant,
elephant.

15:37.569 --> 15:39.071
I forgot my card now.

15:39.104 --> 15:41.573
Six, elephant,
elephant, elephant.

15:41.607 --> 15:43.275
Seven, elephant, elephant--
- Chip?

15:43.309 --> 15:44.777
- Wait, hold on.

15:44.810 --> 15:46.445
one, two, three, four,
five, six, seven,

15:46.478 --> 15:48.914
